## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->
While working with the ExcelJS library, I encountered an issue with date formatting. 
I am using the excel file which has the cell with Date format. 
The value for this cell is `21.10.2014` with chosen format `14.03.2012`>`dd.mm.yyyy``
<img width="412" alt="image" src="https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/assets/100270313/9d19dd06-13f8-498c-bfa8-a8db6cbaf7b7">


Here's a simplified example to illustrate the issue:
```javascript
import ExcelJS from 'exceljs';
import { format } from 'date-fns';

async function readExcelDate() {
  const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
  await workbook.xlsx.readFile('path/to/excel/file.xlsx');
  const worksheet = workbook.getWorksheet(1);
  worksheet.eachRow({ includeEmpty: true }, function(row, rowNumber) {
    const cell = row.getCell(1); // Assuming the date is in the first cell
    const numFmt = cell.numFmt
    console.log(`numFmt - ${numFmt}`);
  });
}

readExcelDate();
```
For this cell in console I see :
`numFmt 'mm-dd-yy'`

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
I expect to have the same format for `numFmt` which I chosen for `Format Cells`
